#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:32
msgid "Base domain"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:33
msgid "Root domain for artist subdomains, e.g. agnosis.art. Each artist is reachable at nicename.{base_domain}. Requires a wildcard DNS record (*.{base_domain}) pointing to this server. Leave blank to disable subdomain routing."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:40
msgid "Debug logging"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:45
msgid "Writes raw diagnostic dumps of the email intake pipeline (message structure, attachment MIME detection, media conversion, post creation) to a dedicated debug directory — far more detail than the Logs tab keeps, for tracing exactly where a submission was rejected or lost. Turn off once you have what you need; files can accumulate quickly. Can also be forced from wp-config.php with `define( 'AGNOSIS_DEBUG', true );`, which overrides this toggle. See the Debug Files panel below for the directory location and a clear-files button."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:50
msgid "Debug file retention (days)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:56
msgid "Debug dumps older than this are permanently deleted by the daily cleanup — automatically, whether or not debug logging is currently turned on, so files left over from a past debug session don't linger indefinitely. A dump is a full raw copy of an artist's email, so this defaults shorter than the inbox/queue retention above. Default: 14 days."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:62
msgid "Preset biography title"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:64
msgid "When set, every artist's biography page uses this exact title instead of their own, regardless of what the artist submitted, edited on their approve form, or later changed on their published page. Leave blank to keep using each artist's own title (the default). Shown exactly as typed here on every language version of a biography page — not machine-translated per language. See \"Include artist's name in preset title\" below."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:68
msgid "Include artist's name in preset title"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:73
msgid "When the preset title above is set, append the artist's own WordPress display name to it (e.g. \"Meet the Artist — Jane Doe\"). Has no effect while the preset title is blank."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:79
msgid "Cloudflare Turnstile site key"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:80
msgid "From your Cloudflare Turnstile widget (dash.cloudflare.com → Turnstile). Adds a human-verification check to the public Subscribe (newsletter-signup) and Join forms. Leave either key blank to leave both forms exactly as they are today."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:84
msgid "Cloudflare Turnstile secret key"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:87
msgid "Kept server-side only — used to verify each form submission directly with Cloudflare before it is accepted."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:101
msgid "Email logo"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:106
msgid "Shown in the header of outgoing HTML emails (submission review, removal confirmation, rejection notice, invitations, and both newsletters) in place of the plain \"✦ Site Name\" text. Leave empty to keep the text wordmark. Displayed at up to 40px tall — any width or aspect ratio works."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:110
msgid "Header background"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:115
msgid "Background color of the colored header bar on every outgoing HTML email."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:119
msgid "Accent color"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:124
msgid "Color of primary buttons and links across every outgoing HTML email. Destructive actions (reject, remove, vote to remove) always use a fixed red regardless of this setting, so they stay visually distinct."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:128
msgid "Email width (px)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:135
msgid "Width of the card every outgoing HTML email is built around. 600px is the long-standing email-safe default most clients render reliably — narrower reads awkwardly on desktop, wider risks getting clipped or horizontally scrolled by some mobile mail apps. Default: 600."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:139
msgid "Page background color"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:144
msgid "Background color that surrounds the email card — the \"letterbox\" area visible in most desktop mail clients. Distinct from the card background below."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:148
msgid "Card background color"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:153
msgid "Background color of the card itself — where the body text and footer sit. Keep this light for readable dark text below; for a dark theme, also darken the text colors."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:157
msgid "Primary text color"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:162
msgid "Default color for body text — the main reading text of every outgoing HTML email."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:166
msgid "Primary text size (px)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:173
msgid "Default base font size for body text. Default: 16."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:177
msgid "Secondary text color"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:182
msgid "Color for muted/secondary text — the footer tagline, work-address descriptions, and small helper links (unsubscribe, notification preferences, \"view online\"). Matches the plugin's original hardcoded footer color, kept as the default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:186
msgid "Secondary text size (px)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:193
msgid "Font size for muted/secondary text — the footer tagline and smaller helper text below the main body copy. Default: 14."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:197
msgid "Footer background color"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:202
msgid "Background color of the footer strip at the bottom of every outgoing HTML email (the tagline, and — on emails that have one — the work-addresses card and unsubscribe/preferences link). Independent of the card background above, so the footer can be set off visually from the body if you like."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:206
msgid "Divider / border color"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:211
msgid "Color of thin divider lines across outgoing HTML email — between the body and footer, above the work-addresses card, and around the newsletter's \"view online\" banner."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:215
msgid "Button text color"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:220
msgid "Text color on the solid accent-colored call-to-action buttons (e.g. \"Confirm subscription\", \"Apply to join\"). Change this alongside the accent color above if you pick a light accent that white text wouldn't read well against."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:224
msgid "Notice box background color"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:229
msgid "Background color of the shaded info/quote boxes used throughout outgoing HTML email — quoted bios and statements, \"did you mean\" suggestions, application summaries, and similar callouts."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:233
msgid "Footer label color"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:238
msgid "Color of the bold address labels (\"Artwork:\", \"Biography:\", etc.) in the work-addresses reference card that appears in the footer of artist-facing notification emails."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:244
msgid "Email driver"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:259
msgid "Mail from: name"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:260
msgid "Name shown as the sender of admission, vote, welcome, departure, invitation, and submission-review emails. Leave blank to use the site name."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:264
msgid "Mail from: email address"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:266
msgid "Dedicated From: address for admission, vote, welcome, departure, invitation, and submission-review emails — e.g. hello@agnosis.art. This is not one of the endpoint addresses below (submit@, bio@, community@, etc.) — those are where artists send mail in; this is who workflow mail appears to come from. Separate from the Settings → Newsletter sender, which only covers digest mail. Leave blank to use the admin email. Must be a valid, deliverable address on your domain (SPF/DKIM configured) or messages may be marked as spam."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:271
msgid "Artwork submissions address"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:272
msgid "Artists send artwork to this address — e.g. submit@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:276
msgid "Biography submissions address"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:277
msgid "Artists send biography updates to this address — e.g. bio@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:281
msgid "Event submissions address"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:282
msgid "Artists send event announcements to this address — e.g. event@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:286
msgid "Replace artwork address"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:287
msgid "Artist sends a new version of an existing artwork. Subject must match the original title. Bypasses duplicate detection — e.g. replace@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:291
msgid "Removal request address"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:292
msgid "Artist requests takedown of an existing artwork. Subject must match the title. Moves the post to draft pending admin review — e.g. remove@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:296
msgid "Promote artwork address"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:297
msgid "Artist sends an email here (subject = exact artwork title) to choose which artwork represents them in the shared community gallery on the main site — not their own subdomain, which already shows everything they've published. Any previously featured artwork is automatically demoted — e.g. promote@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:301
msgid "Photo-only address"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:302
msgid "Opt-out lane for photographers and lens-based artists whose photograph is the artwork, not a snapshot of it. Submissions here are published with the original image exactly as sent — AI enhancement is skipped and the quality-rejection gate is bypassed. AI description (title, tags, alt text) still runs. Use the [Photo] subject indicator as a fallback for mail clients that do not support To: aliases — e.g. photo@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:306
msgid "Pure address (no AI at all)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:307
msgid "Strictest opt-out lane: nothing sent here is touched by AI — no enhancement, no vision description, no rewriting. The published post title, body, and translated-title subtitle are taken verbatim from the artist's own subject and message text; the attached file(s) are published exactly as sent. The quality-rejection gate is bypassed, same as Photo-only. Use the [Pure] subject indicator as a fallback for mail clients that do not support To: aliases — e.g. pure@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:311
msgid "Goodbye / self-removal address"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:312
msgid "Artist emails here (any subject, no attachment needed) to request account deletion. A confirmation link is emailed back before anything is deleted — e.g. goodbye@agnosis.art"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:316
msgid "Community announcement address"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:317
msgid "Any active artist emails here (any subject, no attachment needed) to send a message to every other community member — e.g. community@agnosis.art. Never processed as a submission and never becomes a post: each recipient gets the subject and message translated into their own language, with the sender's name and email included so they can reply directly. Sent from the address configured under Settings → Community → Rules, which can be different from this one. Only works for a message sent by an active, admitted artist."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:323
msgid "IMAP host"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:324
msgid "e.g. imap.yourhost.com"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:328
msgid "IMAP port"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:335
msgid "Use SSL"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:343
msgid "Skip SSL certificate validation"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:348
msgid "⚠ Use only as a temporary workaround when your mail server's certificate is not yet trusted (e.g. Plesk self-signed cert before Let's Encrypt is applied to the mail daemon). Disable this once the mail server presents a valid certificate."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:352
msgid "IMAP username"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:353
msgid "Login username for the IMAP account — typically the catch-all mailbox address."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:357
msgid "Submission email password"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:363
msgid "Webhook secret"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:364
msgid "HMAC secret shared with your webhook provider (Mailgun, SendGrid…). Used for both the inbound-mail endpoint (/wp-json/agnosis/v1/email/inbound) and the bounce/complaint events endpoint (/wp-json/agnosis/v1/email/events) — point your provider's bounce/spam-complaint webhook at the latter to keep your subscriber and artist addresses clean."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:370
msgid "Inbox retention (days)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:376
msgid "IMAP messages and processed/failed queue rows older than this are permanently deleted by the daily cleanup, whether read or unread. Default: 7 days."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:380
msgid "Contact message retention (days)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:386
msgid "Visitor-to-artist contact messages (sent or rejected) older than this are permanently deleted by the daily cleanup. The visitor's IP address is cleared independently after 30 days regardless of this setting, once it's no longer useful for abuse investigation. Default: 90 days."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:392
msgid "Per-sender hourly submission limit"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:399
msgid "Maximum submissions accepted from a single artist per hour, across both IMAP and webhook intake. Exceeding this limit silently drops the message (no retry from ESPs). Default: 5."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:404
msgid "Per-artist contact limit"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:411
msgid "Maximum messages the same visitor (by email address) can send to a single artist within the window below — applies across every language version of that artist's page. Default: 2."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:415
msgid "Per-artist contact limit window (hours)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:422
msgid "Time window, in hours, the per-artist contact limit above applies over. Also controls how long a visitor sees the \"already contacted\" notice instead of the form after messaging an artist. Default: 1 (one hour)."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:427
msgid "Require SPF/DKIM authentication"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:430
msgid "When enabled, intake messages must pass SPF or DKIM authentication (via the Authentication-Results header). Prevents spoofed From: addresses. Requires your ESP to include Authentication-Results headers and your domain to have SPF/DKIM records configured. Leave off if you are not sure — rejected legitimate mail is silent. Default: off."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:436
msgid "Description provider"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:444
msgid "Analyzes the artwork image and writes the title, body, tags and alt text. WordPress AI Services delegates to whichever provider the site has configured via the AI Services plugin."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:448
msgid "OpenAI vision model"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:450
msgid "Model used for artwork description when OpenAI is the description provider. Must support vision input."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:454
msgid "Anthropic model"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:456
msgid "Model used for artwork description when Anthropic is the description provider. Must support vision input."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:467
msgid "OpenAI text model"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:469
msgid "Cheap, fast model used for text-only tasks when OpenAI is the description provider — translating a submission into the site's primary language, and moderating contact-form messages. Does not need vision support."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:473
msgid "Anthropic text model"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:475
msgid "Cheap, fast model used for text-only tasks when Anthropic is the description provider — translating a submission into the site's primary language, and moderating contact-form messages. Does not need vision support."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:479
msgid "Vision image max width (px)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:485
msgid "Images are downscaled proportionally to this width before being sent to the AI for description — vision token cost scales with resolution, and a description task needs far fewer pixels than the original photo. Applies to artwork photo uploads, rasterised PDF pages, and video poster frames alike. Set to 0 to always send full-resolution images (uses more tokens, no quality difference for typical description tasks). Requires the Imagick PHP extension; images are sent at their original size regardless of this setting when it is unavailable. Default: 800."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:491
msgid "Enhancement provider"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:494
msgid "Auto (OpenAI if key is set)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:496
msgid "Disabled — use original image"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:499
msgid "Enhances the artwork image before publishing. Uses OpenAI gpt-image-1. Set to Disabled to skip enhancement and publish the original."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:503
msgid "OpenAI image model"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:505
msgid "Model used for image enhancement when OpenAI is the enhancement provider."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:511
msgid "Polish biography with AI"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:514
msgid "When enabled, biography submissions are passed through the AI to fix spelling and make minor text improvements before saving."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:518
msgid "Polish events with AI"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:521
msgid "When enabled, event submissions are passed through the AI to fix spelling and make minor text improvements before saving."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:527
msgid "Merge biography updates with AI"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:530
msgid "When enabled, biography updates are merged with the existing biography using AI — new information is integrated rather than replacing everything. Recommended: artists can send incremental updates (\"I just won an award\") without resubmitting their full bio. Disable to always replace the biography with the latest submission."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:536
msgid "Rejection threshold (quality score)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:544
msgid "Photos scoring at or below this agnosis_vendor_value (1–10) are automatically rejected — the artist receives a friendly email explaining the issue and is invited to resubmit. Score 0 disables automatic rejection. Must be lower than the enhancement threshold. Default: 3."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:549
msgid "Enhancement threshold (quality score)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:557
msgid "Photos scoring below this agnosis_vendor_value (1–10) are automatically enhanced. Score 10 = perfect photograph, 1 = technically unusable. Default: 7 — only visibly problematic photos are processed. Set to 1 to disable automatic enhancement entirely."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:563
msgid "OpenAI API key"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:566
msgid "Required when OpenAI is the description or enhancement provider."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:570
msgid "Anthropic API key"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:573
msgid "Required when Anthropic is the description provider."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:579
msgid "Artwork display width (px)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:585
msgid "Width of the agnosis-artwork image size used in post content and lightbox. Height scales proportionally. Default: 1920. Existing images need to be regenerated after changing this value."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:589
msgid "Thumbnail size (px)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:595
msgid "Side length of the square agnosis-thumb size used in submission cards and dashboard. Default: 512. Existing images need to be regenerated after changing this value."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:599
msgid "Email image width (px)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:605
msgid "Width of the agnosis-email size used in artist notification emails. Height scales proportionally — no cropping. Default: 420. Existing images need to be regenerated after changing this value."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:611
msgid "Gallery overview — items per page"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:617
msgid "How many artwork cards the gallery overview shows per page. Pool is built proportionally across all artists; featured artworks are preferred. Default: 12."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:623
msgid "Review link expiry (days)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:629
msgid "How long the Approve & Publish / Discard links in a submission review email stay valid before an artist has to log in to manage the item instead. Applies uniformly to artwork, biography, and event drafts. Default: 7."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:635
msgid "System prompt"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:641
msgid "Sent to the AI as the system instruction. Use {tag_count} and {excerpt_words} as tokens — they are replaced with the values below."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:645
msgid "Artist prompt template"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:651
msgid "User message sent alongside the artwork image. Use {artist_prompt} where the artist's own description should appear."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:655
msgid "Enhancement instructions"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:661
msgid "Instructions passed to the image enhancement provider. The AI-generated artwork description is appended automatically as context."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:665
msgid "Number of tags"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:671
msgid "How many tags the AI should generate per artwork. Referenced as {tag_count} in the system prompt."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:675
msgid "Excerpt word limit"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:681
msgid "Maximum words for the one-sentence excerpt. Referenced as {excerpt_words} in the system prompt."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:694
msgid "Trust all admitted artists (skip link review entirely)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:699
msgid "Every artist here was already vouched in by the community — if that trust is enough for you, turn this on to embed any link an artist submits, immediately, with no allowlist check and no AI review at all (the settings below are skipped entirely while this is on). Off by default. Only enable this if you are comfortable that a bad actor who made it through admission could embed a link to anything."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:703
msgid "Trusted embed platforms"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:709
msgid "One hostname per line. A submitted link becomes a rich embed immediately if it matches one of these (or a subdomain of one) — no AI review needed, no network request made to the link itself."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:713
msgid "Let artists submit other links too (AI-reviewed)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:718
msgid "When enabled, a link to a site not on the trusted list above is not simply discarded: the destination page is fetched and reviewed by your configured AI provider (Settings → AI Providers) against the categories below before deciding whether to embed it. If the AI cannot be reached, the request times out, or the page cannot be safely fetched, the link is not embedded — it fails safe. When disabled (the default), only the trusted platforms above are ever embedded."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:722
msgid "Block pornographic / sexually explicit content"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:727
#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:745
msgid "Only takes effect when AI review (above) is enabled."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:731
msgid "Block primarily commercial / promotional sites"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:736
msgid "Online stores, advertising, marketing landing pages. Off by default — an artist linking to a shop selling their own prints is common and not inherently unwanted. Only takes effect when AI review (above) is enabled."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:740
msgid "Block gambling / betting sites"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:749
msgid "Additional disallowed categories"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:754
msgid "Optional — describe any other kind of content the AI should reject, in plain language (e.g. \"hate speech or violent extremist content\", \"phishing or scam pages\"). Only takes effect when AI review (above) is enabled."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:760
msgid "Node label"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:761
msgid "How this node introduces itself to the network."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:766
msgid "Enable ActivityPub federation"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:770
msgid "Broadcast new artworks to Mastodon, Pixelfed and the Fediverse."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:775
msgid "Node public key"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:777
msgid "Auto-generated RSA public key for this node. Share this with peer nodes."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:787
msgid "Self-removal (goodbye) requests per sender per day"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:793
msgid "Maximum number of self-removal (\"goodbye\") confirmation emails a single sender address can trigger per day. A genuine self-removal only ever needs to be requested once — this caps how many confirmation emails a spoofed or repeated From can be used to spam a real artist with. Default: 3."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:797
msgid "Community broadcasts per artist per day"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:803
msgid "Maximum number of messages a single artist can send to the Community announcement address (Settings → Email) per day. Prevents one member from flooding every other member's inbox. Default: 3."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:807
msgid "Community broadcast max length (characters)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:814
msgid "Longer messages to the Community announcement address are bounced back to the sender instead of being broadcast — the sender is told to shorten it and resend. Measured in characters, not words, so it applies fairly across languages that don't use spaces between words (Chinese, Japanese, Thai, etc.). Every recipient's copy is translated individually, so this also caps how much a single message can cost in AI translation calls. Default: 2000. Hard maximum: 20000, regardless of this setting."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:845
msgid "Admin approval only (disable community voting)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:850
msgid "When enabled, artists can no longer vouch new applicants in or vote to remove a member — every admission and removal decision is made directly by an admin instead (Settings → Community → Pending Applications / Members). Applications wait indefinitely for an admin decision rather than auto-rejecting when no one can vote. A community removal vote already open when this is turned on still runs to its normal conclusion; only starting a new one is blocked. Off by default — most communities want the existing vouching/vote system."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:855
msgid "Admission vote threshold (%)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:860
msgid "Percentage of active artists that must vote yes for admission. Combined with the minimum floor below."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:864
msgid "Admission minimum votes"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:868
msgid "Absolute minimum positive votes required regardless of the percentage above."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:872
msgid "Voting window (days)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:876
msgid "Days an application stays open. If the threshold is not reached within this window the application is rejected."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:880
msgid "Resolved application retention (days)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:886
msgid "A rejected, withdrawn, or left application's email, name, biography, statement, and portfolio link are anonymized by the daily cleanup after this many days — the application record itself (status and dates) is kept for admission history. A banned artist's biography/statement/portfolio are anonymized on the same schedule, but their email is deliberately kept so the ban stays enforceable. Default: 180 days."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:890
msgid "After applying, send artists to"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:894
msgid "Optional — pick a page explaining the vouching process and what happens next. When the application is submitted successfully, the artist is redirected there instead of just seeing an inline confirmation message. Leave as \"None\" to keep the inline message only."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:898
msgid "Community size cap"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:902
msgid "Maximum number of admitted artists. When full, new applications join a waitlist instead of being rejected, and a freed slot admits the next in line. Set to 0 for no cap. The community can also vote to change this."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:906
msgid "Cap-change co-signers required"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:910
msgid "How many artists must co-sign a proposal to change the community size cap before it opens as a full community vote."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:914
msgid "Cap-change vote window (days)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:918
msgid "Days a community cap-change vote stays open. A strict majority of active artists voting yes adopts the new cap."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:922
msgid "Removal nominations required"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:928
msgid "Number of artist nominations needed before a community removal vote opens. Admins can bypass this threshold."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:932
msgid "Removal vote window (days)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:938
msgid "Days a community removal vote stays open. A majority (>50%) of active artists must vote yes for removal to proceed."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:942
msgid "Invitation intro"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:946
msgid ""
"Agnosis is a small, self-hosted home for artists who'd rather make work than manage a platform. There's no algorithm deciding who sees your art, no portfolio site to maintain, and no account to configure — just your work, published and translated automatically for a global audience.\n"
"\n"
"Being part of the community is simple: Fellow artists vouch for new applicants, and everyone keeps full ownership of what they publish; you can leave at any time and take your work with you.\n"
"\n"
"Once admitted, you submit new work by sending it as an email — no dashboard, no forms and you can update, promote or remove your artwork as well sending an email. You can find more information visiting the agnosis.art website."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:951
msgid "Shown near the top of the \"Send Invitation\" email below (an \"Apply to join\" link and site name follow automatically — no need to add either here). Two or three short paragraphs is plenty. Standing copy, not cleared after use like the newsletter intros above — translated automatically when an invitation is sent in a language other than the site's own."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:957
msgid "Transaction fee (%)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:962
msgid "Percentage retained by this node on donations and art sales. Artists pay nothing up front."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:970
msgid "Sender name"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:971
msgid "Name shown as the sender of digest emails. Leave blank to use the site name."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:975
msgid "Sender email address"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:977
msgid "Dedicated From: address for both newsletters, e.g. newsletter@agnosis.art — keeps digest mail separate from the site's admin email for deliverability and so artists can filter it. Leave blank to use the admin email. Must be a valid, deliverable address on your domain (SPF/DKIM configured) or messages may be marked as spam."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:981
msgid "Auto-draft newsletter intros"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:986
msgid "When enabled, Agnosis drafts an intro via AI ahead of each issue (see the lead time below), saves it to that newsletter's intro field, and emails you to review it — unless you've already written one for that cycle. Disable to leave both intro fields exactly as you left them, always."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:990
msgid "Draft intro this many hours ahead"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:996
msgid "How long before an issue is due Agnosis proposes an AI-drafted intro. Only takes effect when auto-drafting (above) is enabled. Default: 24."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1000
#: includes/Newsletter/Scheduler.php:386
msgid "Artist newsletter"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1003
msgid "Admitted artists are auto-enrolled (they can unsubscribe from any issue with one click). Community digest: recent activity, new members, open votes."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1007
msgid "Artist newsletter frequency (days)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1013
msgid "Default 30 ≈ monthly. A new issue is prepared once this many days have passed since the last one was sent."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1017
msgid "Artist newsletter intro"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1021
msgid "Optional note prepended to the next artist issue only — cleared automatically once that issue is queued. Leave blank to send the auto-digest with no intro. If left blank, Agnosis drafts one automatically from what's new about a day before the issue sends, and emails you to review it first — write your own here any time to skip that."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1025
#: includes/Newsletter/Scheduler.php:386
msgid "Public newsletter"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1028
msgid "Visitors subscribe via the agnosis/newsletter-signup block (double opt-in). Digest: new artwork and events published since the last issue."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1032
msgid "Public newsletter frequency (days)"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1038
msgid "Default 30 ≈ monthly."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1042
msgid "Public newsletter intro"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1046
msgid "Optional note prepended to the next public issue only — cleared automatically once that issue is queued. If left blank, Agnosis drafts one automatically from what's new about a day before the issue sends, and emails you to review it first — write your own here any time to skip that."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1050
msgid "Send batch size"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1056
msgid "Recipients emailed per 5-minute cron tick. Lower this if your host throttles outbound mail; raise it for faster delivery on hosts with generous limits."
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1060
msgid "Self-hosting comfort threshold"
msgstr ""

#: includes/Admin/SettingsFields.php:1066
msgid "Advisory only — self-hosted sending keeps working above this count. Once confirmed public subscribers pass it, this page shows a reminder to consider an email service provider (e.g. Brevo's free tier) instead."
msgstr ""

